					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-636292#post-2357778</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-636292/scp-1309#post-2357778</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Fri, 14 Aug 2015 23:50:48 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Kuraden</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>2236849</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>So the temporal displacement is 90% perception, and 10% physical,</p> <p>But what happens to D-Class who are experimentally 'integrated' into the town right before the cycle resets?</p> <p>It's brilliant, but I feel the foundation would insist on meddling with what causes someone to become 'trapped' in the loop, and unable to leave the displacement.</p> <p>Upvoted, top shelf stuff, but I'd love more experimentation in what makes this thing tick.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
